		<td width="10%" nowrap="nowrap">Post subject:&nbsp;</td>
		<td><b>Re: Anyone remember the first NES emulator?</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tineras wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I should say that the real reason I'm asking is because I'm wondering what the slowest hardware is that you could run a NES emu on. </div>
<br />That depends on the target platform's display model. PocketNES runs on the 16.8 MHz ARM7 in a Game Boy Advance, but it helps that the GBA PPU has a video mode to which the NES PPU's display model maps fairly nicely. The GBA CPU emulates the NES CPU, the mapper chip, and about 10% of the NES PPU and APU, and the GBA PPU and APU emulate the rest.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


