	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I had Nesticle running on a Intel 486 based CPU PC (yeah that one with awful FM MIDI sound), that was already obsolete in the early 2000 years (I was an early teenager).
<br />I don't remember the speed of the CPU, but I know that PC was made in 1994, and that was a very high-end one back then (probably why it was still functional working in the early 2000 years !). I had it working again last year when I was taking the opportunity that I bought a notebok to definitely got rid of all old desktop PCs of the house, and of course I tried Nesticle on it for nostalgia. It was a bit lagging.
<br />Too bad I don't remember the CPU speed, but the PC has 16 MB RAM, and the CPU on it was probably one of the best available in the year 1994.

		

		</td>
