		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />That guy is Paul Robson, he made some <a href="http://www.ticalc.org/archives/files/fileinfo/120/12080.html" class="postlink">nice TI83 software</a> as well.  I had no clue he made NES emulators.
<br />
<br />According to some website I'm reading called <a href="http://www.emuwiki.com/index.php?title=The_Emulation_Timeline" class="postlink">"The Emulation Timeline"</a>, VSMC (snes emulator) existed back in September 1994, but that website doesn't list any NES emulators before 1997.  The first NES emulator it mentions is "Nes Lord".

		

